Pattern mining in node-attributed social networks focuses on extraction of patterns, e.g. subsets of specific attributes or connections\footnote{An example of a pattern is a maximal clique . Recall that  a clique is a subset of nodes in an undirected graph such that every two nodes are adjacent.  A clique is called maximal if there is no other clique that contains it.}, in network structure and attributes . Among other things, this helps to make sense of a network and to understand how it was formed. In the context of community detection, the extracted patterns are used as building blocks for communities.  
